bout the Book0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis innovative volume effectively combines curricular themes and teaching methods to provide practical teaching tools for international studies faculty. The broad range of substantive issues addressed in the book reflects the diversity of actors—national, regional, and international—that respond to global problems. The authors explore new techniques for covering these issues, focusing on the case method, games, simulations, role-play exercises, and uses of technology. Emphasizing linkages between theory and practice, each chapter features classroom activities designed to engage students and encourage critical thinking. Teaching tips and a list of additional resources, submitted by members of the International Studies Association, complete this distinctive handbook.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh1 aBoehrer, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoehrer, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBonham, G. Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoyer, Mark A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCallahan, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCusimano, Maryann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonick, Lev, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHagan, Joe D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaney, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHey, Jeanne A. K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHobbs, Heid